  "texts": [
    "To simplify, these readout error probabilities are set to be constant for all qubits and time.",
    "Dark-blue regions of low infidelity (with the minima marked with a red star) do not coincide with the state infidelity calculated using the global average of experimentally measured readout calibrations (marked by a black dot).",
    "This disparity that either the target experiments experienced initialization or measurement errors at a higher rate than measured by simpler calibrations and/or fitting with potentially incorrect A-matrices yields a highly non-positive state that is mapped to a high-fidelity physical state under constrained optimization.Combining readout mitigation with tomography thus remains an open question for further work, and the results of the main text are limited by unaddressed readout error on terminal measurements.",
